article.headline: McCoughtry scores 28 as No. 16 Louisville cruises
article.linkText: McCoughtry scores 28 as No. 16 Louisville cruises
article.story:
LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- Angel McCoughtry scored a career-high 28
points and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead Louisville (No. 16 ESPN/USA Today; No. 17 AP) to a 70-58
win over Western Kentucky on Saturday.

Yuliya Tokova had 13 points and nine rebounds and Patrika Barlow
added 11 points, six rebounds and four assists as Louisville (9-0)
took control early then held off a second-half surge by the Lady
Toppers (5-3).

Western Kentucky's Crystal Kelly battled foul trouble in the
first half but finished with 20 points. The Lady Toppers, however,
made just 4 of 27 shots from 3-point range and shot 32 percent from
the floor on the game.

Louisville won despite committing 21 turnovers -- the third
straight game the Cardinals have given the ball away at least 20
times -- and making just one 3-pointer.

Western Kentucky trailed by 14 at the half, but closed within
41-36 midway through the second half. The Cardinals, however,
responded behind McCoughtry and Tokova to pull away.

The Cardinals raced to a 20-point lead, scoring the game's first
12 points as the Hilltoppers missed their first seven shots from
the field. It didn't get much better for Western, which shot an
anemic 24 percent in the first half as it struggled to shoot over
Louisville's zone.

The Lady Toppers came into the game shooting 41 percent from
3-point range on the season, but missed their first 10 shots from
behind the arc.

Only some sloppy ballhandling by the Cardinals allowed the
Hilltoppers to keep it competitive. Louisville turned the ball over
a dozen times in the first half, but still led 32-18 at the break.
